// ---- PAGE 5: Minutes 1-2 ----
#mcr-eyebrow("Settle · Notice")
= Minutes 1–2: Arrive and Notice

#mcr-lead[Begin by landing in the day, then let one thought step forward.]

#mcr-group[Minute 1 — Arrive]
You are not behind yet. This first minute is about landing in the day — feeling
the chair or floor beneath you, noticing the light, letting your shoulders drop.
There is nothing to fix. You are simply here, at the start.

#mcr-field("What am I carrying into this morning?", lines: 2)

#mcr-group[Minute 2 — Notice]
Most mornings offer a crowd of thoughts at once. You are not going to sort all
of them. Pick the one that keeps tapping you on the shoulder, and simply look at
it. For now you are observing it, not solving it.

#mcr-field("What thought is taking up the most space?", lines: 2)

#mcr-panel[
  A single sentence is enough on either line. These first two minutes are about
  arriving and noticing — not about writing well.
]
#pagebreak(weak: true)
